==English==

===Noun===
'''[[abessive]] [[case]]'''

#{{grammar}}: [[case]] used to express the [[lack]] and [[absence]] of something. It has the meaning of the English preposition "without." Some languages that use the abessive case are [[Erzya]], [[Estonian]], [[Finnish]], and [[Inari Sami]].

====Synonyms====
*[[caritive case]]

